          "type": "tool_use",
          "name": "Write",
          "input": {
            "content": "# Ledger Snapshot Tool Design\n\n## Purpose\n\nA testing tool that runs every sensible command and option combination against a\ngiven Ledger data file, capturing output to individual files. This creates a\nbehavioral snapshot that can be diffed before/after a code change to detect\nunintended side effects across all reporting surfaces.\n\n## CLI Interface\n\n```\npython test/snapshot.py <ledger-binary> <data-file> <output-dir> [options]\n\nPositional arguments:\n  ledger-binary     Path to the ledger executable\n  data-file         Path to the journal/data file to test against\n  output-dir        Directory to write output files (created if needed)\n\nOptions:\n  --jobs N          Parallel workers (default: CPU count)\n  --mine-from DIR   Source tree root to mine combos from\n                    (default: auto-detect from ledger binary location)\n  --timeout SECS    Per-invocation timeout (default: 30)\n  --dry-run         Print all combos without running them\n  --verbose         Print progress to stderr\n```\n\n## Combination Generation Strategy\n\n### Curated Combinations\n\nEach command is tested with every individual relevant option, plus curated\nmulti-option combos that test known interactions.\n\n**Commands tested:** `balance`, `register`, `print`, `csv`, `xml`, `emacs`,\n`accounts`, `payees`, `commodities`, `prices`, `pricedb`, `tags`, `stats`,\n`equity`, `budget`, `cleared`\n\n**Option categories applied per command:**\n\n- **Universal** (most report commands): `--flat`, `--empty`, `--real`,\n  `--cleared`, `--uncleared`, `--pending`, `--current`, `--collapse`,\n  `--subtotal`, `--no-total`, `--invert`, `--dc`, `--related`, `--generated`,\n  `--depth 2`, `--wide`, `--average`, `--percent`, `--count`, `--aux-date`,\n  `--by-payee`, `--no-rounding`, `--no-titles`, `--exact`, `--raw`\n- **Period**: `--daily`, `--weekly`, `--monthly`, `--quarterly`, `--yearly`,\n  `--dow`\n- **Valuation**: `--market`, `--basis`, `--gain`, `--quantity`, `--price`,\n  `--historical`\n- **Lot**: `--lots`, `--lot-prices`, `--lot-dates`, `--lot-notes`,\n  `--lots-actual`\n- **Sort/limit**: `--sort date`, `--sort amount`, `--sort payee`, `--head 5`,\n  `--tail 5`\n- **Command-specific**: `--budget`/`--unbudgeted` for balance/register,\n  `--anon` for print, etc.\n\n**Curated multi-option combos** (known interactions):\n- `--monthly --market`, `--monthly --empty`, `--monthly --collapse`\n- `--flat --depth 2`, `--flat --empty`\n- `--market --gain`, `--market --historical`\n- `--budget --empty`, `--budget --monthly`\n- `--sort date --flat`, `--subtotal --by-payee`\n- `--basis --lots`, `--market --monthly --empty`\n- Plus additional combos (~20-30 total curated multi-option sets)\n\nNot all options apply to all commands. Options are tagged with applicable\ncommands; inapplicable combos are not generated.\n\n### Mined Combinations\n\nReal-world command+option combos are extracted from three sources:\n\n1. **Test files** (`test/baseline/*.test`, `test/regress/*.test`,\n   `test/manual/*.test`): Parse `test <command>` lines\n2. **Texinfo manual** (`doc/ledger3.texi`): Extract ledger invocations from\n   `@smallexample` blocks\n3. **Man page** (`doc/ledger.1`): Extract example invocations\n\n**Stripping rules** applied to all mined combos:\n- Remove `-f <file>` arguments and file paths\n- Remove query/account arguments (anything not a `--flag` or its value)\n- Keep only the command name + options\n\n**Deduplication:**\n- Normalize option order (sort alphabetically)\n- Canonical form: `(command, frozenset(options))` where value-bearing options\n  are `(\"--depth\", \"2\")` tuples\n- Deduplicate against curated set and against each other\n\n### Coverage Validation\n\nAfter generating all combinations, the tool verifies:\n1. Every known command appears in at least one combination\n2. Every known option appears in at least one combination\n\nMissing commands/options get fallback combinations added automatically.\n\n### Expected Scale\n\n- Curated: ~500-1500 combinations\n- Mined (after dedup): ~500-2000 unique combinations\n- Total: ~1000-3500 combinations (well within the tens-of-thousands budget)\n\n## Execution Engine\n\nEach combination is invoked as:\n\n```\nledger --args-only --columns 80 -f <data-file> <command> <options>\n```\n\n- `--args-only` prevents reading `~/.ledgerrc` (hermetic execution)\n- `--columns 80` ensures stable output width\n- Workers run via `concurrent.futures.ProcessPoolExecutor(max_workers=jobs)`\n- Per-invocation timeout produces a file recording the timeout\n- Uses `subprocess.run` with `capture_output=True`\n\n## Output Format\n\n### File Naming\n\nAll output files are written to a flat `output-dir/`:\n\n- `<command>--<opt1>--<opt2>--...txt` with options sorted alphabetically\n- Value-bearing options encode their value: `--depth-2`, `--sort-date`\n- Bare command: `balance.txt`, `register.txt`\n- Hyphens in option names preserved: `--by-payee` stays `by-payee`\n- Filenames exceeding 255 bytes are truncated with a hash suffix\n\n### File Content\n\n```\n# Command: ledger --args-only --columns 80 -f sample.dat balance --flat\n# Exit code: 0\n<stdout>\n# --- stderr ---\n<stderr if any>\n```\n\n### Progress and Summary\n\nWith `--verbose`, a progress counter prints to stderr. On completion, a summary\nis printed: total combinations run, successes, errors, timeouts.\n\n## Implementation\n\n- Single Python file: `test/snapshot.py`\n- Python 3.10+ (consistent with existing test harness)\n- No external dependencies beyond the standard library\n- Reuses patterns from existing `test/LedgerHarness.py` (env sanitization,\n  subprocess management)\n\n## Diffing Workflow\n\n```bash\n# Before changes:\npython test/snapshot.py ./build/ledger test/input/sample.dat /tmp/before\n\n# After changes:\npython test/snapshot.py ./build/ledger test/input/sample.dat /tmp/after\n\n# Compare:\ndiff -r /tmp/before /tmp/after\n```\n",
